Started with the floor, now we’re here. 

First, we binned the bag. Then we cut the cord. Now we’re working on relieving you from cleaning altogether. How? By aiming to create the UK’s largest, most advanced robotics centre. And with it, Dyson-designed robots and autonomous devices for your home. 

#Dyson #DysonRobotics #InsideDyson #Innovation #Robots

Issey Miyake | 1938 – 2022

James Dyson said: “Issey Miyake was a brilliant designer and creator. His pieces were unlike anyone else’s and his influence on the fashion industry will be felt for decades to come. 

“I developed an admiration for his work as I visited Japan over many years, and we formed a bond, collaborating a number of years ago when he invited me to design a Paris show for his new collection. The theme was ‘Wind’, and my set design was to mirror that of the ingenious clothing Issey and his team had created – all based around Dyson vacuum cleaners. It was an extraordinary project, for which I am thankful to him and his willingness to try something new. He will be greatly missed by the design world. My thoughts are with his close colleagues and friends.” 

First encountering his work in 1985, James Dyson admired Miyake’s bold approach to design. In 2007, Miyake and Dyson collaborated on the runway presentation of ‘The Wind’, the designer’s Spring/Summer collection of that year.
